  "text": "EASY EVERYDAY is almost out in the world! In just four days, it will be here! I am so excited to share this book baby with you. I have to say, I truly think it is my best book yet. It has all the fabulous parts of Everyday Dinners, but ALL sorts of recipes. Breakfast, lunch, dinner, snacks, desserts, drinks and more! It would mean everything to me if you would preorder a copy today! If so, you will have it on Tuesday and we can cook through it together! If you prefer to shop small, you can order locally through bookshop. You can also order a signed copy through my own local bookstore here! Perfect Easter basket filler or Mother’s Day gift! Also: did you know I have a cookbook club where we cook through the book and have fun challenges and giveaways? There is currently a huge giveaway happening right now! We’ve been doing this since 2017! On instagram, I have done some sneak peeks of recipes that you can make today! My blueberry iced lattes, grilled watermelon bruschetta, lunchtime tuna orzo and cherry jalapeño chicken salad. Events If you are local to the Pittsburgh area, you can come to the Easy Everyday launch signing on Tuesday, April 15th at 7PM! RSVP here! Annnd P.S. if you happen to be on Nantucket in July (or feel like planning a trip), I’ll be signing books with Elin Hilderbrand on Wednesday July 16th! More details to come. Bonus Cookbook! If you preorder the book, you get my FREE BONUS COOKBOOK that has 15 brand new 20-minute recipes! Preorder your copy, then fill out this form to get the cookbook instantly delivered to your email! Inside EASY EVERYDAY, you will find: Over 100+ effortless recipes for everyday life. An assortment of all sorts of recipes, many of them meatless and vegetarian. My 10-minute meal prep strategy for EVERY recipe. My pantry and fridge essentials, aka the recipes I can’t live without. They change the game for easy meals. My tips and tricks for how to get a meal on the table for your family, consistently and in an enjoyable way, without stress! Low-maintenance, uncomplicated dishes! How to repurpose leftovers. All of my usual ramblings and of course, photos for everything. Woohoo! These are just a few of the delicious recipes inside the book! Amazon / Barnes \u0026 Noble / Bookshop.org / Books A Million Target / Hudson Booksellers / Apple Ebook / Google Play Ebook  Per usual, you’ll get to enjoy so many of my favorite classics with a modern twist in Easy Everyday. And I can’t wait for us to chat all about it!",
